buttons.snippet: Pure vodka tastes fairly neutral and has a full-bodied mouthfeel. One common way to drink this alcoholic beverage is to take shots of vodka from shot glasses at room temperature. When drinking high-quality vodkas, consider sipping the liquid slowly from a tumbler glass.

buttons.subtitle: What Is Vodka Usually Made From
buttons.title: How Vodka Is Made: Inside Vodka's Production Process - MasterClass
buttons.snippet: Traditional vodka is made from two raw materials: water and ethanol from the fermentation of cereal grains (like wheat, sorghum, or rye). Many vodka brands use other base ingredients (like potatoes and sugar beets) and additives (like botanicals and spices) to achieve distinctive character in their liquor.
snippet_highlighted_words: water and ethanol from the fermentation of cereal grains (like wheat, sorghum, or rye)
